                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>President Truman on June 26, 1948, signed <gloss target="#t_HR1">HR</gloss> 6556,
                    the Trade Agreements Extension Act of 1948 (62 Stat. 1053) which continued the
                    program for one year and contained provisions which the President felt would
                    “hamper and obstruct the negotiation of new agreements”. For the text of
                    President Truman’s statement, see: <hi rend="italic">Public Papers of the
                        Presidents: Harry S. Truman: 1948</hi> (Washington: Government Printing
                    Office, 1964), pages 385–386. On October 5, 1948, the President signed an
                    executive order prescribing revised procedures for administering the trade
                    agreements program. For text see: Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, October 17, 1948, pages 502–503.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
